claim.claim-text:
53. The method of claim 51, wherein: 
the step of varying the thickness of selected portions of the tubular member includes: 
mounting the tubular member on a rotating mechanism; 
rotating the tubular member; 
contacting the outer surface of the tubular member with a cutting device which removes selected amounts from the tubular member until the desired thickness is achieved in select portions of the tubular member.

54. A method of manufacturing a strut assembly having variable thickness, comprising: 
selecting a strut pattern; 
determining flexing portions and stable portions for the strut pattern; 
forming a strut assembly with the desired strut pattern; 
providing at least some flexing portions of the strut pattern of the strut assembly with a nominal thickness; and 
providing at least some stable portions of the strut pattern of the strut assembly with a greater-than-nominal thickness.
